Gns1g8lON4I.description:
With the Divine Blessings of Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba, the Episode-13 of monthly lecture series gama ãgama will be delivered by  Professor Ana Sarasvati Konjar

The Vedas – the foundation of Indian Culture & Spirituality Episode-XIII

The lecture series is intended to disseminate the Vedic knowledge and also to recollect and introspect Swami’s teachings as food for thought for individual transformation with regular practice. 

“The chief requisite of man’s life is to be human. Whatever your scholarship or position of authority, you should not ignore the human values. Indian culture is unparalleled and most wonderful. Having forgotten the grandeur and glory of their heritage, the students of today enticed by so-called modernity, have become oblivious to their own innate divinity.

The whirlwind of the rapidly progressing science and technology, coupled with industrialization, is bringing about undesirable changes in our society by way of uprooting the moral or ethical values so essential for human well-being. Science and technology have, no doubt, contributed substantially to material progress; but they have altogether undermined spiritual values such as selflessness, divinity, and dignity inherent in man. In a way, they have devalued humanity itself so much so that the present generation of young men and women are unable to recognise their divine nature. They are considering self-centredness as the goal of life. Demonic qualities like ostentation, egoism, and excessive and empty talk are playing their devil dance in society.

This very country, which has been the spiritual teacher of entire mankind, is becoming the playing field of evil forces like injustice, indiscipline, licentiousness, and defiance of truth. Having become slaves to modernity, people are utterly disregarding truth and righteousness and ignoring the Indian culture and traditions, with the false notion that material self advancement is the ‘summum bonum’ of life. What the students have to protect today is not the nation. They have to safeguard truth and righteousness only. These two, in turn, will protect the nation. Giving up truth and righteousness, educated persons nowadays are causing damage to the nation, ostensibly in the name of protecting it.” - Summer Showers 1990-Bhagawan Sri Sathya Sai Baba

With the Divine Blessings, the“ Śrī Sathya Sāī Sam̆ yukta Śruti Śreṇi ” brings you, Episode # 13 of once a month lecture series entitled gama ãgama to disseminate the Vedic knowledge because the Vedas are the repositories of Indian culture.

The lecture series intends to provoke thought based on the teachings of Bhagawan Baba on how to harmonise the ancient culture with the needs of the modern world to lead life governed by truth, righteousness, and peace and above all, love toward all living being. This platform provides an exposure to students to Indian culture, along with their normal studies to acquaint themselves with the knowledge of spirituality for practice.

6JysS8Wh-l8.title: Seminar - Careers In Civil Services
6JysS8Wh-l8.description:
With the immense divine blessings of our beloved, Bhagwana Sri Sathya Sai Baba, a session on "Careers in Civil Services" was organised on 1st August 2021 on an online platform, with its agenda on cracking the prestigious Union Public Services Commision (UPSC) exam, as aspired by millions of youth from all over the nation since years, with the aim of inspiring and guiding the youth of Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation on achieving it and thus forseeing the reigns of the nation to be, in the hands of men and women of great morale and strong character at the service of men and women of the country in the years to come.

The session was commenced at 9.35 AM, with the lightening of the lamp by beloved Bhagawan. Under the considerate moderation by Dr. Gopi Krishna Pidatala , the context setting of the programme was done by the All India President of Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India, Respected Nimish Pandya. The session was then guided by five highly experienced, distinctly decorated Officers from the Central Government (India):

1) Sri. LV Subrahamanyam IAS (Retd) ; Former Chief Secretary, Govt.of Andhra Pradesh

2) Dr. AVS Ramesh Chandra IFS ; Add. Secretary, Ministry of External Affairs GOI

3) Smt. A. Sridevasena IAS, Commissioner of Education , Govt. Of Telangana

4) Sri. J. Krishna Kishore, prl Commissioner, Income Tax, GOI

5) Sri.V.Gopala Krishna, Director Brain Tree IAS Academy, Hyderabad

A total of 300 participants connected and were guided, which was later concluded by the Question and Answers Sessions and Shanti Mantram offering at the Divine Lotus Feet.

Jai Sai Ram

--7OXrGZyOo.title: UNICEF Collaborates with Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India.Video Message of Sri Nimish Pandya
--7OXrGZyOo.description:
UNICEF collaborates with the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations,India and Sri Sathya Sai Central Trust, Prasanthi Nilayam to create an awareness and propagate the authentic information in the prevention & post-Covid measures. Sri. Nimish Pandya, All India President of Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation, in a video message, narrated the scale of relief operations undertaken by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation in length and breadth of India in domains of hunger alleviation and safety by providing food  for nearly 20 Million people most of the beneficiaries being migrate labours. Face masks, PPE kits, milk, water bottles etc were also distributed in big numbers.

The Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India through  online training programme is scheduled to train 4,000 volunteers in 4 batches where in from  Andhra Pradesh 2000 Sevadals, Telangana 1000 sevadals and from Karnataka 1000 sevadals are being trained in the first phase  

In the second phase, members of Sevadals from Tamil Nadu and Kerala will undergo this online training later on Sri Sathya Sai Sevadals from all over India will be trained. The sevadals will be reaching out to the communities and general public through every possible mode of communication.

Here is the video Message of the Sri Nimish Pandya, All India President, speaking on the initiative being taken up along with the details of Seva done by the Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India during the pandemic .

Jai Sai Ram
Press and Media Team
Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India
--7OXrGZyOo.channelTitle: Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India

4qQmS--NsRc.title: Sri Sathya Sai Community Kitchens
4qQmS--NsRc.description:
With the onset of the crippling coronavirus affecting millions around the world, life has come to a standstill, many nations are facing #lockdown.
With restriction of movement, came #hunger and unemployment. Such imposition also meant that various charitable organisations like SSSSOIndia couldn't render their services.
But where there is a will, there is a way.
Adhering to all instructions on social distancing and hygiene protocol laid down by the Government of #India, the Sri Sathya Sai #CommunityKitchens, with 111 kitchens and 29,000 volunteers, have so far, been able to serve 1.47 million #meals to those in need.

9XcEmJ8CDQ8.title: Ganesh Visarjan
9XcEmJ8CDQ8.description:
As we bid goodbye to our beloved Lord Ganesha, may His divine blessings bestow upon us.
The tradition of visarjan serves as a reminder that everything we possess is temporary and that we shall have to do away with it sooner or later. Through the visarjan, devotees bid farewell to the idol of God, but the presence of the divine stays on, in the form of energy/essence.
This visarjan let it not be a journey from our homes to the sea, but from our altar to our hearts.

Sanitation Service at Edayaranmula, Pathanamthitta

Conducted by Sri Sathya Sai Model Village, Kottuppara and District Legal Service Authority (DLSA)
Pathanamthitta)

Shri.Jayakrishnan(Sub Judge, DLSA) inaugurated this event and he was with us throughout for the effort.

100 kg of bleaching powder were also distributed for the cleaning purpose.

Sairam

TnluNiDfmlA.title: Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations,  Save & Serve, Day 4 at Edanad, Chengannoor
TnluNiDfmlA.description:
4th Day (27-08-2018)

Sanitation Service at Edanad, Chengannoor.

Conducted by Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisation, Kottayam
 
As per the sevadals today was a golden day. Edanad, Chengannur was very badly affected by the floods and the clay accumulated after it. Here the first people to come for the service was from Sri Satya Sai Seva Organisation, Kottayam. Pllease dont hesitate to do good things when we get a chance as GOD is making us an instrument to do such good deeds.

* Done cleaning in many houses
* Done Super chlorination in many wells in that houses
*Cleaning helped those house mates to go back to their life n daily routine
*Cleaned and sanitised the houses of bedridden patients,widows,patients,Old people, and even for those who are staying alone at their houses...
* Given counselling for those women who are psychologically affected after this bad call of nature...

we have also supplied 150 Nos Sai Premadhara kits to the inhabitants of such cleaned house for their well being and happy living and also prayed for their welfare.

100 kg of bleaching powder were also distributed for the cleaning purpose.
TnluNiDfmlA.channelTitle: Sri Sathya Sai Seva Organisations, India
